info.title: Account Service
info.description: Account management offers a holistic view of the customer, and allows you to capture, monitor, store and track all critical business information about customers and prospects.

servers.description: Example of server url is https://my1234567.crm.cloud.sap

get.description: Specify query parameters to return desired account records from the system.

parameters.name: $top
parameters.description: Show only the first n accounts.

parameters.name: $search
parameters.description: Search for a string within accounts.

parameters.name: $count
parameters.description: Indicates if count of accounts to be returned.

parameters.name: $query
parameters.description: Run a specific query in account service.

400.description:
Bad Request.

The server cannot process the request due to a client error. For example, an invalid request.

401.description:
Unauthorized.

This error is caused when the request has not been applied because there are no valid authentication credentials for the target resource.

403.description: User is not authorized to query accounts in the system. Check user's authorization under Settings - Users and Control - Business Roles

500.description:
Internal Server Error.

Failed to query accounts.

501.description: The server does not support the functionality required to fulfill the request.

post.description: Send account information to the system to create a new account.

two.summary: Create an account with default Address, Account Team member, and Relationship.

201.description: A new account is created in the system.

400.description: Account is not created in the system. The request sent to the system is invalid.

401.description: User is not authenticated to create a new account in the system.

403.description: User is not authorized to create an account in the system. Check user's authorization under Settings - Users and Control - Business Roles

500.description: Failed to create an account due to an internal server error.

get.description: Read a specific account using the account ID.

200.description: Account with the requested ID is found in the system.

400.description: Invalid Request. Failed to read the account information.

401.description: User is not authenticated to read the account information in the system.

403.description: User is not authorized to read account information in the system. Check user's authorization under Settings - Users and Control - Business Roles

404.description: Account with the request ID is not found in the system.

500.description: Failed to read the account due to an internal server error.

patch.description: Update account attributes in the system.

parameters.name: If-Match
parameters.description: Used for conflict management when a consumer tries to update a resource. This parameter checks if the state of the resource known to the client (etag) matches the state on the server and if true, allows the update to continue.

one.summary: Update of Account Status and name

400.description: Invalid request. Failed to update the account.

401.description: User is not authenticated to update the account in the system.

403.description: User is not authorized to update the account in the system. Check user's authorization under Settings - Users and Control - Business Roles

412.description: Failed to update the account. The account was updated in a parallel session. Try again with a new if-match http header value.

428.description: Failed to update the account. The mandatory http header if-match was not sent in http request header.

500.description: Failed to update the account due to an internal server error.

x-sap-shortText: Manage entities from the account service

x-sap-extensible.description: You can create extension fields in the account API by following the steps mentioned in https://help.sap.com/docs/CX_NG_SVC/2c87cece32844c91836e535aef8f9642/d3bdfac0c6b141c0bac27408c3ed159f.html?locale=en-US. The newly created extensions will be available in the API request and response body.
